dcterms:description: The MIT-BIH Database contains heart rate measurements for four different individuals, used to evaluate various forecasting models.
dcterms:title: MIT-BIH Database

dcterms:description: T1 is a heart rate time series dataset containing 1800 equally spaced instant heart rate readings (in beats per minute) obtained at intervals of 0.5 seconds.
dcterms:title: T1 (Heart Rate time series dataset)

dcterms:description: T2 is a heart rate time series dataset similar to T1, also containing 1800 equally spaced instant heart rate readings (in beats per minute) obtained at intervals of 0.5 seconds.
dcterms:title: T2 (Heart Rate time series dataset)

dcterms:description: T3 is a heart rate time series dataset containing 950 heart rate measurements obtained at intervals of 0.5 seconds.
dcterms:title: T3 (Heart Rate time series dataset)

dcterms:description: T4 is a heart rate time series dataset containing 851 heart rate measurements obtained at intervals of 0.5 seconds.
dcterms:title: T4 (Heart Rate time series dataset)
